    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -\nNorth Florida Baseball dropped its midweek game against Bethune-Cookman, 7-4, at Harmon Stadium on Tuesday.\nJunior outfielder\nGialdri Gomez\nnotched his third multi-hit game in his last four outings. Gomez went 2-4 with two RBI and one walk against BCU.\nBethune-Cookman opened the scoring with two runs in the fourth inning and three in the fifth. However, North Florida showed immense fight to cut its deficit to just one.\nGomez drove in North Florida's first run of the game in the bottom of the sixth frame with a single to shortstop. North Florida's biggest inning at the dish came in the bottom of the seventh to bring it within one run of BCU.\nRedshirt sophomore outfielder\nCarter White\ncrushed an RBI triple off the wall in right field to plate senior\nSantiago Ordonez\nwho reached on a walk. White crossed home from third base on a fielding error by Bethune-Cookman. North Florida scored its final run of the inning\u00a0on Gomez' second single to shrink BCU's advantage to 5-4.\nBethune-Cookman responded with two runs in the eighth frame, bringing the score to its eventual final.\nNORTH FLORIDA 4, BETHUNE-COOKMAN 7\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nJulian Carrasquilla (1-0)\nLoss:\nTyler Kozera\n(0-2)\nLine Scores\nBETHUNE-COOKMAN\n| 7 R, 11 H, 3 E\nNORTH FLORIDA\n| 4 R, 7 H, 2 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nGialdri Gomez\n| 2-4, 2 RBI, 1 BB\nCarter White\n| 1-3, 1 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nSean Benjamin\n| 1-4, 1 RBI, 1 R, 1 BB\nBoone Hosey\n| 1-3, 2 BB\nTyler Kozera\n| 3.1 IP, 5 H, 2 R, 2 ER, 2 K, 1 BB\nBETHUNE-COOKMAN\nJeter Polledo | 2-5, 2 RBI, 2 RBI, 2 R\nJulian Carrasquilla | 5.1 IP, 2 H, 1 R, 1 ER, 4 K, 3 BB\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida opens Atlantic Sun Conference play on the road at Stetson from March 13-15. First pitch for Game 1 on Friday is set for 6:30 p.m. ET."
